default9.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default Having all offences handled via one single platform provides the additional benefit of efficient and accurate reporting.
default&#xa0;defaultEvidence for consideration:default10.
default 
defaultA 
defaultStarTraq
default system has the ability to automatically read a vehicle registration mark and offence details using optical character recognition (OCR) and automatic number plate 
defaultrecognition (ANPR) on both analogue and digital offences. Alternatively, if ANPR data 
defaultis provided by the camera technology then this can be uploaded to a 
defaultStarTraq
default system 
defaultand displayed alongside the offence image.
default11.
default 
defaultThe System can be deployed securely on the Cloud, so it is ideal for remote locations 
defaultsuch as level crossings.
default12.
default 
defaultWith a direct connection to the Police National Computer (PNC) a 
defaultStarTraq
default system 
defaultcan check the vehicle and keeper identity reporting back to the verifier the keeper's 
defaultaddress details and the current status of the vehicle (for example, if it has been 
defaultreported stolen).
default13.
default 
defaultThe 
defaultStarTraq
default system can display multiple images and video clips to the verifier. Image 
defaultenhancement tools allow the verifier to accurately record offences. Rejection codes 
defaultfor exempt vehicles (such as police, ambulance and fire engines) can be used so that 
defaultan outcome for every offence is achieved.
default14.
default 
defaultThe output from 
defaultStarTraq
default system is a comprehensive file of driver names, addresses 
defaultand date of birth along with offence details ready for processing. This output file can 
defaultalso be 
defaultcustomised
default ready to export to a 3rd party system, such as education course 
defaultprovider.
default15.
default 
defaultTools for adding officer issued tickets to the database are also available.
default16.
default 
defaultA 
defaultStarTraq
default system will help Network Rail to:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultProcess offences without the need for adding to headcount thereby keeping costs down and guaranteeing a return on investment.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCentralise
default processing of offences maintaining the flexibility to allow for multi-
defaultsite operations.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOperate a system that is flexible, user friendly and dynamic.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCustomise
default the workflow to map a process bespoke to Network Rail/BTP 
defaultautomating much of the offence lifecycle.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGive confidence that a 
defaultStarTraq
default system is camera vendor independent 
defaultsoftware supporting interfaces from all camera types.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultProvide a seamless diversion of offenders to court or driver education —
defaultdetermined by Network Rail.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultProvide court files at the click of a button.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFuture proof
default a system protecting against any legislation and camera hardware 
defaultchanges.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultReduce on-going IT support costs.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSend correspondence in multiple languages to offenders and/or refer offenders 
defaultto a website for trusted translation.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultView offence images online and any other details that Network Rail/BTP deem 
defaultappropriate.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFully integrate with handheld devices or scan paper tickets supporting process 
defaultofficer manually generated issued tickets.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOffer e-learning as part of an overall driver education strategy. 
defaultRecommendation:default17.
default 
defaultStarTraq's
default recommended solution to support level crossing safety improvements is for 
defaultNetwork Rail and its enforcement partner (BTP) to 
defaultadopt an enforcement protocol that 
defaultis fair, transparent, trusted and reliable. A 
defaultStarTraq
default system will provide a sophisticated workflow and document management capability Network Rail to process level crossing 
defaultoffences from different camera types through to a successful outcome e.g. fine, 
defaulteducation or court.
default18.
default 
defaultStarTraq
default recommends that Government looks to introduce an enforcement solution for 
defaultlevel crossing safety, drawing on the results and benefits that have been gained by 
defaultother enforcement agencies. By taking a targeted approach to casualty reduction 
defaultwhere education and enforcement work together, compliance at level crossings will be 
defaultachieved.
default19.
default 
defaultLastly 
defaultStarTraq
default recommends that the Office of Rail Regulator (ORR) works with the 
defaultParliamentary Advisory Council for Transport Safety and Royal Society for Prevention 
defaultof Accidents (
defaultRoSPA
default) to devise a comprehensive package of educational courses 
defaultaimed at Level Crossing offenders so that road users are offered a real alternative to a fixed penalty once an offence has been committed.
